Quote:  Just when it was growing dusk and when Thomas was becoming a little anxious about his companion's ability to reach Galt's at Marairua, they breasted the top of a ridge and saw a beautiful stretch of sloping ridges covered with silver tussock and almond grass, facing the sun.

<i>Ibid.</i> 101  All the country was very rough, with scrub, fern and tutu mixed with native grass, especially long green almond grass, which made splendid cattle feed.
